FBIS4-30467 "dreas124_i_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 Cambodia Sam Rangsi Against Outlawing Khmer Rouge Sam Rangsi Against Outlawing Khmer Rouge BK2806061094 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 27 Jun 94 BK2806061094 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia Cambodian BFN [Text] Mr. Sam Rangsi, vice chairman of the FUNCINPEC [National United Front for an Independent, Neutral, Peaceful, and Cooperative Cambodia] party and economy and finance minister of the two-headed government, stated that he supported Foreign Minister Norodom Sirivut's position that outlawing the Khmer Rouge is contrary to the king's idea. Mr. Sam Rangsi said that if the National Assembly ratifies this law next July all the budget will be used for military purposes and none will be left for national reconstruction.
